In today's globalised world, ''cross-cultural communication'' competence is crucial for successful international negotiations. Understanding the cultures involved and adapting to different communication styles are key. Failure to address cultural differences can lead to breakdowns in communication. Cross-cultural competence requires recognising and respecting cultural differences, effectively managing diversity, and fostering unity for successful negotiations.
